  <meta content="Creating a Campaign form in Experience Manager 6.1 or 6.2" name="jcr:title" />
  <meta content="With the Adobe Experience Manager 6.1 or 6.2 integration, you can create forms directly in AEM to create and update profiles or manage subscriptions." name="seoDescription" />
 </head>
 <body>
  <p>You can create "forms" on your AEM sites and map the fields in a form to the fields in the Adobe Campaign database. This allows you to create and update profiles or manage the subscriptions to a service.</p> 
  <p>To create an Adobe Campaign form on your AEM site:</p> 
  <ol>
   <li><p>In your AEM site, create a new page based on the <strong>User Profile Page, powered by Adobe Campaign</strong> template.</p> </li>
   <li><p>In the page properties, select the <strong>Cloud Service</strong> corresponding to your Adobe Campaign instance.</p> </li>
   <li><p>Select the form type from the <strong>Form Start</strong> component: save profile, subscription to a service or unsubscription from a service.</p> </li>
   <li><p>Edit the content of the form by adding different fields and components that you can map to the Adobe Campaign database fields.</p> </li>
   <li><p>Test and publish the form to make it accessible on your AEM site.</p> </li>
  </ol>
  <p>For more information, refer to the <a href="https://docs.adobe.com/docs/en/aem/6-2/author/personalization/adobe-campaign/adobe-campaign-forms.html">detailed documentation</a>.</p> 
